					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5973571#post-3836952</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5973571/scp-3662#post-3836952</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 15 Jun 2018 20:04:09 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Decibelles</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2005044</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>This is really hard-hitting. By the end of it, I felt invested in every single aspect of the story. For such a benign anomaly, you really took it places. And while I can't imagine how this will tie into the rest of your series, I think it's strong enough on its own merits to warrant an upvote. The interview was very well-done, as was the newspaper clipping. That sealed the deal for me.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5973571#post-3825798</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5973571/scp-3662#post-3825798</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 05 Jun 2018 20:04:49 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Anorrack</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>4188420</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>The SPC admits to using the bird meme to try to combat &quot;Selachian Entities,&quot; but it didn't work. with this article it states that persons trapped inside would be very sensitive to aberrant memes in the noosphere, ergo a person came into contact with the bird meme while inside the clock, and when extracted, spread the meme, causing the apocalypse.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5973571#post-3808011</guid>
