					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5973571#post-3806600</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5973571/scp-3662#post-3806600</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sun, 20 May 2018 13:41:11 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Ayers</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1856789</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Hi, ribby!</p> <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">[+]&nbsp;My&nbsp;response</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">[-]&nbsp;My&nbsp;response</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <p>The newspaper is an addition for a couple reasons:</p> <ul> <li>Provides a second point for the story to click for people.</li> <li>Attempts to explain some common follow-up questions like &quot;why didn't her parents notice?&quot;</li> <li>Adds another emotion to the equation (not only did Light get away with this, he's also <em>regarded as a hero</em>. What an asshole.)</li> </ul> </div> </div> </div> <br /> But, yeah, I can understand it feeling heavy-handed. I lack the kind of talent to make stuff like this feel natural. Thank you for your thoughts!
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
